rComments: This course is broad and I think he has worked hard to get things organized by topic for students to be able to follow. As long as you study from his notes, which are provided, things are clear. I found the midterm totally fair when studying like this. The assignments have been challenging, but everything is doable. Love this class.
Just writes lots of equations without explaining them, read through the textbook to learn properly
This is a first year class and the prof just seems to ramble on making material even more complex than it needs to be. He has notes but is extremely hard to follow. Do not take his class.

I am new to this course. I understand it is his first time teaching 151, but he is getting paid and should still maintain professionalism. He is disorganized & basically just writes down equations on the board without explanation.
The tests are difficult even if you try to study for them (so don't bother to study for them). Not worth taking the class unless you absolutely have to.
Kushner was a decent prof. The class was fairly easy overall, and he presented material in a clear and concise manner.
Great prof. Very clear and organized lecture notes, good explanation of concepts. Prepares you well for tests. Approachable and helpful.

Unless you know what you're doing and are familiar with the material before it's taught, Kushner's lectures are a confusing verbiage extremely difficult to follow. Assignment solutions are never posted and the course has no mercy for those who are "slow" to learn. I feel like I'm going to forget the material a few weeks after the course is over.
He tried his best. Sometimes not really clear, but he did try to help as much as he could. Anyways, the course was really hard, so overall he did an ok job.
